The breakfast was excellent, but only having the choice of an eye-watering expensive restaurant (but good), is not really good enough.	Breakfast was good - usual continental style plus scrambled eggs and bacon, cereals, fresh fruit and champagne!	The breakfast buffet was simply amazing - abundant, varied and delicous food, beautifully presented and offered with gracious, attentive service.	The buffet is well presented but is fairly standard and not at all up to the level of the Michelin-starred restaurant.	The breakfast offered a fine selection of warm and cold food, fruit and a traditional Italian pastry.	The restaurant situated in the hotel is nice but expensive, a glass of chardonnay was suggested (25,- euro's per glass).